result.execSummary:
The defendant Danny E. Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Neglecting a Child - Specified Harm Did Not Occur and Child Under 6 Years of Age [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Notice of Assignment of Judge - Return to Sender, Refused, Unable to Forward
Reminder Notice indicating amount due mailed to defendant.

(Cases 22CF506, 21CF350 are called at 11:33 AM) Defendant Danny E. Davis in court, in custody.   Attorney Travis S. Gaetz in court for Danny E. Davis. Attorney Matthew Kirkpatrick in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defense acknowledges receipt of Information in 22CF506, waives reading. Defense indicates there is an agreement and recites the joint sentence recommendation. Court revokes the Deferred Acceptance of a Guilty Plea Agreement in 21CF350 and finds the Defendant guilty. 
Defendant pleads Guilty to 22CF506 Count 1- Neglecting a Child as Repeater. Defendant acknowledges prior convictions. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Court accepts plea and finds the Defendant guilty. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in. 
Court orders 36 months Probation with the following conditions: 9 months jail on Count 1 in 22CF506 with No Huber privileges, all but first 20 days stayed pending further order of the court- Court orders if Treatment Court Program is not completed, remaining jail be served with Huber; No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting; Comply with Department of Human Services regarding K.D. and G.W.; Participate in and successfully complete Eau Claire County Treatment Court Program; Maintain absolute sobriety; Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations; Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge; Court costs. 6 days jail credit, if revoked in 22CF506. No jail credit, if revoked in 21CF350.
